This paper is about machine reading and reasoning using memory networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces a novel mechanism inspired by the connection short-cutting principle in computer vision, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper involves training the model in an end-to-end fashion, which is a common approach in deep learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
